<item>
            <title>[LU-603] NFS get permission deny on RHEL5-x86_64 and i686 mixed architecture</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-603</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Both NFS v3 and v4 cannot work on 64bit and 32bit mixed architecture, get permission deny on NFS client.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;NFS v3:&lt;br/&gt;
----------------&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;root@client-15 ~&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;# more /etc/exports &lt;br/&gt;
/mnt/lustre     *(rw,all_squash,anonuid=500,anongid=500)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;root@client-5 ~&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;# mount -t nfs -o vers=3 10.10.4.15:/mnt/lustre /mnt/lustre&lt;br/&gt;
mount: 10.10.4.15:/mnt/lustre failed, reason given by server: Permission denied&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <environment>lustre server: RHEL5-x86_64&lt;br/&gt;
lustre client(nfs server): RHEL5-i686&lt;br/&gt;
nfs client: RHEL5-i686</environment>
